==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Head-hunter
<hw>Head"-hunt`er</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧d"h⟦ucr⟧nt`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of any tribe or race of savages who have the
custom of decapitating human beings and preserving their heads as
trophies. The Dyaks of Borneo are the most noted head-hunters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person whose profession is to find executives to
fill open positions in corporations; an executive personnel recruiter;
also, a company that performs a similar service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Head"-hunt`ing</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Headily</ent>⟦br⟧
